ints":2,"statements":[{"text":"...","isTrue":true},{"text":"...","isTrue":false}]},\n    {"id":"c","text":"<question>","type":"FILL_IN","points":1,"acceptedAnswers":["answer1","answer2"]}\n  ],\n  "difficulty": <1-5>,\n  "estimatedDurationSec": <number>\n}	{\n  "title": "Weekend Weather Forecast",\n  "listeningType": "monologue",\n  "transcript": "Good morning, everyone! I'm Sarah Mitchell, and here's your weekend weather forecast. So, let's start with Saturday. Well, it's going to be a bit of a mixed day, actually. The morning will be quite cloudy with some light rain expected, especially in the north of the country. Temperatures will be around 12 degrees Celsius, so you know, not exactly warm. Make sure you grab a jacket if you're heading out early. By the afternoon, though, the clouds should clear up and we might get some sunshine — but don't get too excited, because the wind will be picking up, reaching speeds of about 40 kilometres per hour in coastal areas. Now, Sunday looks much more promising. We're expecting a mostly dry and sunny day across the whole country. Temperatures will rise to about 18 degrees, which is actually quite nice for this time of year. However, there is a chance of thunderstorms in the evening, particularly in the south, so if you're planning any outdoor activities, I'd recommend doing them in the morning or early afternoon. And just a heads up — next week is looking pretty cold again, with temperatures dropping back to around 8 degrees. So enjoy the sunshine while it lasts! That's all from me — stay safe and have a great weekend!",\n  "speakers": [{"id":"1","name":"Sarah Mitchell","gender":"female"}],\n  "contextPL": "Usłyszysz prognozę pogody na weekend przedstawioną przez prezenterkę radiową.",\n  "question": "Listen to the weather forecast and answer the questions below.",\n  "subQuestions": [\n    {\n      "id": "a",\n      "text": "What does the forecaster say about Saturday afternoon?",\n      "type": "CLOSED",\n      "points": 1,\