o to bed around 11 PM, though sometimes I stay up a bit later if I have homework.  That's basically my routine!", "speed": 0.92, "voice": "en-GB-Neural2-A", "speaker": "Kasia", "pauseAfterMs": 500}], "contextPL": "Usłyszysz, jak dziewczyna opisuje swoją codzienną rutynę w dni szkolne.", "transcript": "Hi, I'm Kasia, and I'd like to tell you about my typical weekday routine. Well, I usually wake up around 6:30 in the morning, which is, you know, quite early, but I need time to get ready for school. First, I have a quick shower and brush my teeth – I spend about fifteen minutes in the bathroom. Then I go downstairs and have breakfast with my family. We usually have some bread, cheese, and coffee. It's nothing fancy, but it's important to eat something before school, right? I leave home at around 7:45 and take the bus to my high school. The journey takes about twenty minutes. Classes start at 8:15, and I have six lessons every day. During lunch break, which is around noon, I eat in the school cafeteria with my friends – we usually grab a sandwich or something quick. After school finishes at 2:30, I either go to the gym or I study at home. Actually, I try to exercise three times a week because I want to stay fit. On other days, I do my homework and revise for exams. In the evening, around 6 o'clock, we have dinner together as a family. After that, I relax – maybe I watch Netflix or scroll through my phone for a bit. I usually go to bed around 11 PM, though sometimes I stay up a bit later if I have homework. That's basically my routine!", "subQuestions": [{"id": "a", "text": "What time does Kasia usually wake up on weekdays?", "type": "CLOSED", "points": 1, "options": [{"id": "A", "text": "6:00 AM"}, {"id": "B", "text": "6:30 AM"}, {"id": "C", "text": "7:00 AM"}, {"id": "D", "text": "7:45 AM"}], "correctAnswer": "B"}, {"id": "b", "text": "Decide if the statements are TRUE or FALSE:", "type": "TRUE_FALSE", "points": 2, "statements": [{"text": "Kasia takes the bus to schoo