cmo7poij8000cvtrgbf1dndfq	cmnnavx1i0002vtm0tr0pj4hs	cmnz8xq400001vtro3l6p4ibw	LISTENING	1	4	{"audioUrl": "https://matury-online-audio.s3.eu-north-1.amazonaws.com/listening/live_2c753fd1-d362-4a42-835f-4aa5be11aee6.mp3", "maxPlays": 2, "question": "Listen to the weather forecast and answer the questions below.", "segments": [{"text": "Good evening, and welcome to your weekend weather forecast.  Well, it looks like Saturday is going to be a pretty mixed day, actually.  We'll start off with some sunshine in the morning, but don't be fooled — clouds will move in by early afternoon, and we're expecting some light rain from around two o'clock.", "speed": 0.92, "voice": "en-GB-Neural2-B", "speaker": "David", "pauseAfterMs": 500}, {"text": "Temperatures will reach a maximum of about fifteen degrees, so it's not exactly warm, you know.  Make sure you grab a jacket if you're heading out.  Now, Sunday is looking a lot more promising.", "speed": 0.92, "voice": "en-GB-Neural2-B", "speaker": "David", "pauseAfterMs": 500}, {"text": "The rain will clear overnight, and we should see blue skies for most of the day.  It'll be a bit warmer too — we're looking at around nineteen degrees, which is quite nice for this time of year.  There might be a light breeze in the evening, but nothing too strong.", "speed": 0.92, "voice": "en-GB-Neural2-B", "speaker": "David", "pauseAfterMs": 500}, {"text": "So, if you're planning any outdoor activities this weekend, I'd definitely recommend going for Sunday rather than Saturday.  And one more thing — next week is looking pretty unsettled overall, with storms possible from Tuesday onwards.  So, enjoy the Sunday sunshine while you can!", "speed": 0.92, "voice": "en-GB-Neural2-B", "speaker": "David", "pauseAfterMs": 500}, {"text": "That's all for tonight.  Have a great weekend.", "speed": 0.92, "voice": "en-GB-Neural2-B", "speaker": "David", "pauseAfterMs": 500}], "contextPL": "Usłyszysz prognozę pogody na nadchodzący weekend prezentowaną przez prezentera telewizyjnego.", "transcript": "Good evening, and welcome to your weekend weather forecast. Well, it looks like Saturday is going to be a pretty mixed day, actually. We'll start off with some sunshine in the morning, but don't be fooled — clouds will move in by early afternoon, and we're expecting some light rain from around two o'clock. Temperatures will reach a maximum of about fifteen degrees, so it's not exactly warm, you know. Make sure you grab a jacket if you're heading out. Now, Sunday is looking a lot more promising. The rain will clear overnight, and we should see blue skies for most of the day. It'll be a bit warmer too — we're looking at around nineteen degrees, which is quite nice for this time of year. There might be a light breeze in the evening, but nothing too strong. So, if you're planning any outdoor activities this weekend, I'd definitely recommend going for Sunday rather than Saturday. And one more thing — next week is looking pretty unsettled overall, with storms possible from Tuesday onwards. So, enjoy the Sunday sunshine while you can! That's all for tonight. Have a great weekend.", "subQuestions": [{"id": "a", "text": "What does the forecaster say about Saturday afternoon?", "type": "CLOSED", "points": 1, "options": [{"id": "A", "text": "It will be sunny and warm all day."}, {"id": "B", "text": "There will be heavy storms starting at noon."}, {"id": "C", "text": "Rain is expected to begin in the early afternoon."}, {"id": "D", "text": "The temperature will drop below ten degrees."}], "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"id": "b", "text": "Are the following statements TRUE or FALSE?", "type": "TRUE_FALSE", "points": 2, "statements": [{"text": "Sunday will be warmer than Saturday.", "isTrue": true}, {"text": "The forecaster recommends Saturday for outdoor plans.", "isTrue": false}, {"text": "Next week is expected to bring unsettled weather with possible storms.", "isTrue": true}, {"text": "On Sunday evening, strong winds are forecast.", "isTrue": false}]}, {"id": "c", "text": "Complete the sentence. On Sunday there might be a light ________ in the evening.", "type": "FILL_IN", "points": 1, "acceptedAnswers": ["breeze", "light breeze"]}], "listeningType": "monologue", "audioDurationMs": 33684}	[Live generated] Weekend Weather Forecast	PP	t	0	0	2026-04-20 21:33:03.572	2026-04-20 21:33:03.572
